Cut off and discard wing tips. Cut each wing in half at joint. Rinse under cold running water, pat dry with paper towel. Place in a 9 x 13 inch baking dish. In a bowl combine honey, hot sauce, honey mustard, soya sauce, canola oil, ginger and garlic, mix well. Pour over wings. Cover and refrigerate 6 hours or overnight. Preheat oven to 400 degrees F. Place chicken wings and sauce in a single layer on foil 15 x 10 inch baking sheet. Bake 40 - 50 minutes until browned.